[SN]TITLE[SN]
Marlow woman 'set on fire' after suffering fatal head injury

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman suffered a fatal head injury before her body was set alight, police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Albertina Choules, 81, was attacked at her home in Ragmans Lane, Marlow, in the early hours of Wednesday.
A 23-year-old man from High Wycombe has been arrested on suspicion of murder and is in custody.
A family statement described the victim, known as Tina, as a "self-sufficient" woman who was "incredibly special".
